HEADWORD: Kinsfolk
<hw>Kins"folk`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Relatives; kindred;
kin; kinfolk; persons of the same family or closely related
families.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They sought him among their <qex>kinsfolk</qex> and
acquaintance.</q> <rj><qau>Luke ii. 44. </qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kinshasa</ent>⟦br⟧
